A Discord.js framework that just works.



## About `reciple` A Discord.js framework that just works. ## Help ``` Usage: reciple [options] [command] The CLI for reciple Options: -v, --version Output the CLI version number -D, --debug Enable debug mode (default: false) --no-debug Disabled debug mode --env Load environment variables from .env file (default: []) -h, --help display help for command Commands: build [options] Build the reciple modules defined in config file create [options] [output] Create a new reciple project start [options] Start the reciple client help [command] display help for command ``` ## Installation ```bash npx reciple yarn dlx reciple pnpx reciple bunx reciple deno run -A npm:reciple ``` ## Links - [Website](https://reciple.js.org) - [Discord](https://discord.gg/KxfPZYuTGV) - [Github](https://github.com/reciplejs/reciple/tree/main/packages/reciple) - [NPM](https://npmjs.org/package/reciple)
